        public static DirFileTree getTree​(TreeFile file)
                           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                  java.io.IOException
        Returns a DirFileTree of the root directory of the given file.
        If a file tree was already created with the given path, then the old file tree is returned.

        This function replaces the constructor.
        Parameters:
        file - The root directory of the file tree.
        Returns:
        A file tree starting at the the root directory the given class originates from.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If the given file is not a directory.
        java.io.IOException - If the root directory could not be accessed.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
